;leeeeetle box

INUMBER 957
NAME 363
WEIGHT 3
VOLUME 2
MISC
SUBSTANCE WOOD
*DESCRIPTION_START
You see an ornately carved wooden box with a lid of thin white wood, so highly polished that you can see right through it. A cleverly carved latch secures the lid for carrying. A pair of bone pointers lay in the center of the box, where they can be easily pulled out and turned in the hand to be tossed back into the box. A small hollow at either end holds scoring stones for the players. Surrounding the hollow, ten small pictures of woodland beasts are covered by tiny slivers of bark. A central pouch holds scoring stones for the players. [Please tap to have a GM activate the box (temporary)]
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFVERB TAP -1
 ECHO PLAYER Our operators are all busy at the moment, please be patient. Your call is important to us.
 GMMSG **%n has requested that the Aelfen Game be activated, please compile JACKGAME.SCR, thank you.
ENDIF


;BIG box

VARIABLE BOXGAME1
VARIABLE BOXGAME2
VARIABLE BOXGAME3


INUMBER 957
NAME 363
WEIGHT 3
VOLUME 2
MISC
SUBSTANCE WOOD
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 1
OPENABLE
LATCHABLE
TURNABLE
*DESCRIPTION_START
You see an ornately carved wooden box with a lid of thin white wood, so highly polished that you can see right through it. A cleverly carved latch secures the lid for carrying. A pair of bone pointers lay in the center of the box, where they can be easily pulled out and turned in the hand to be tossed back into the box. A small hollow at either end holds scoring stones for the players. Surrounding the hollow, ten small pictures of woodland beasts are covered by tiny slivers of bark. A central pouch holds scoring stones for the players.
*DESCRIPTION_END



IFPREVERB TAP -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 OPEN
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = ITEMVAL2
   EQUAL FLAG3 0
   ECHO PLAYER You tap the right side of the board...
   ECHO OTHERS %n taps the right side of the board...
   STRCVT 0 ITEMVAL4
   ECHO ALL You see %0 stones in the hollow on that side.
   IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Deer is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT2 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Falcon is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT3 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Raven is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT4 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Eagle is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT5 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Owl is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Bat is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT7 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Cat is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT8 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Snake is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT9 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Boar is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
    ECHO ALL The carving of Wolf is uncovered.
    ADD FLAG3 1
   ENDIF
   IFVAR FLAG3 = 10
    ECHO ALL All ten totems are uncovered!
    IFVAR ITEMVAL4 > ITEMVAL5
     ECHO PLAYER You have won the game!
     ECHO OTHERS %n has won the game!
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = ITEMVAL3
    EQUAL FLAG3 0
    ECHO PLAYER You tap the left side of the board...
    ECHO OTHERS %n taps the left side of the board...
    STRCVT 0 ITEMVAL5
    ECHO ALL You see %0 stones in the hollow on that side.
    IFVAR ITEMBIT11 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Deer is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT12 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Falcon is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT13 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Raven is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT14 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Eagle is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT15 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Owl is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT16 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Bat is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT17 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Cat is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT18 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Snake is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT19 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Boar is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR ITEMBIT10 = 1
     ECHO ALL The carving of Wolf is uncovered.
     ADD FLAG3 1
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG3 = 10
     ECHO ALL All ten totems are uncovered!
     IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > ITEMVAL4
      ECHO PLAYER You have won the game!
      ECHO OTHERS %n has won the game!
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ELSE
    IFVAR ITEMVAL2 = 0
     EQUAL ITEMVAL2 INTNUM3
     ECHO PLAYER You tap the right side of the board, indicating your seat.
     ECHO OTHERS %n taps the right side of the board, indicating %h seat.
    ELSE
     IFVAR ITEMVAL3 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMVAL3 INTNUM3
      ECHO PLAYER You tap the left side of the board, indicating your seat.
      ECHO OTHERS %n taps the left side of the board, indicating %h seat.
     ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You reach over and tap the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n reaches over and taps the board.
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You must open it first.
 ENDIF
ENDIF


IFPREVERB PULL -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = ITEMVAL2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You pick up the two intricately carved, bone pointers, one in each hand.
  ECHO OTHERS %n picks up the two intricately carved, bone pointers, one in each hand.
  EQUAL FLAG4 1
 ELSE
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = ITEMVAL3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You pick up the two intricately carved, bone pointers, one in each hand.
   ECHO OTHERS %n picks up the two intricately carved, bone pointers, one in each hand.
   EQUAL FLAG4 1
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TURN -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
  EQUAL FLAG4 0
  EQUAL BOXGAME3 0
  ECHO PLAYER You twirl the pointers about between your fingers, releasing them to fly into the box.
  ECHO OTHERS %n twirls the pointers about between %h fingers, releasing them to fly into the box.
  RANDOM BOXGAME1 1 4 0
  RANDOM BOXGAME2 1 4 0
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 1
   ECHO ALL The first bone pointer points north.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 2
   ECHO ALL The first bone pointer points east.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 3
   ECHO ALL The first bone pointer points south.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 4
   ECHO ALL The first bone pointer points west.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 1
   ECHO ALL The second bone pointer points north.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 2
   ECHO ALL The second bone pointer points east.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 3
   ECHO ALL The second bone pointer points south.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 4
   ECHO ALL The second bone pointer points west.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 1
   IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 1
    EQUAL BOXGAME3 1
    ECHO ALL This pattern is called Deer's Antlers.
   ELSE
    IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 3
     EQUAL BOXGAME3 2
     ECHO ALL This pattern is called Falcon's Stoop.
    ELSE
     IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 4
      EQUAL BOXGAME3 3
      ECHO ALL This pattern is called Raven's Flight.
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 2
   IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 2
    EQUAL BOXGAME3 4
    ECHO ALL This pattern is called Eagle's Eyes.
   ELSE
    IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 3
     EQUAL BOXGAME3 5
     ECHO ALL This pattern is called Owl's Strike.
    ELSE
     IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 4
      EQUAL BOXGAME3 6
      ECHO ALL This pattern is called Bat's Wings.
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 3
   IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 1
    EQUAL BOXGAME3 7
    ECHO ALL This pattern is called Cat's Paws.
   ELSE
    IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 3
     EQUAL BOXGAME3 8
     ECHO ALL This pattern is called Snake's Fangs.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME1 = 4
   IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 2
    EQUAL BOXGAME3 9
    ECHO ALL This pattern is called Boar's Tusks.
   ELSE
    IFVAR BOXGAME2 = 4
     EQUAL BOXGAME3 10
     ECHO ALL This pattern is called Wolf's Claws.
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 0
   ECHO ALL This is not a pattern.
  ELSE
   IFVAR INTNUM3 = ITEMVAL2
    IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 1
     IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT1 1
      ECHO PLAYER You uncover the picture of Deer on your side of the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n uncovers the picture of Deer on %h side of the board.
     ELSE
      IFVAR ITEMBIT11 = 0
       ADD ITEMVAL4 1
       ECHO PLAYER You place a stone in the hollow on your side of the board.
       ECHO OTHERS %n places a stone in the hollow on %h side of the board.
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 2
     IFVAR ITEMBIT2 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT2 1
      ECHO PLAYER You uncover the picture of Falcon on your side of the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n uncovers the picture of Falcon on %h side of the board.
     ELSE
      IFVAR ITEMBIT12 = 0
       ADD ITEMVAL4 1
       ECHO PLAYER You place a stone in the hollow on your side of the board.
       ECHO OTHERS %n places a stone in the hollow on %h side of the board.
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 3
     IFVAR ITEMBIT3 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT3 1
      ECHO PLAYER You uncover the picture of Raven on your side of the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n uncovers the picture of Raven on %h side of the board.
     ELSE
      IFVAR ITEMBIT13 = 0
       ADD ITEMVAL4 1
       ECHO PLAYER You place a stone in the hollow on your side of the board.
       ECHO OTHERS %n places a stone in the hollow on %h side of the board.
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 4
     IFVAR ITEMBIT4 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT4 1
      ECHO PLAYER You uncover the picture of Eagle on your side of the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n uncovers the picture of Eagle on %h side of the board.
     ELSE
      IFVAR ITEMBIT14 = 0
       ADD ITEMVAL4 1
       ECHO PLAYER You place a stone in the hollow on your side of the board.
       ECHO OTHERS %n places a stone in the hollow on %h side of the board.
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 5
     IFVAR ITEMBIT5 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT5 1
      ECHO PLAYER You uncover the picture of Owl on your side of the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n uncovers the picture of Owl on %h side of the board.
     ELSE
      IFVAR ITEMBIT15 = 0
       ADD ITEMVAL4 1
       ECHO PLAYER You place a stone in the hollow on your side of the board.
       ECHO OTHERS %n places a stone in the hollow on %h side of the board.
      ENDIF
     ENDIF
    ENDIF
    IFVAR BOXGAME3 = 6
     IFVAR ITEMBIT6 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT6 1
      ECHO PLAYER You uncover the picture of Bat on your side of the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %n uncovers the picture of Bat on %h side of the board.
     ELSE
      IFVAR ITEMBIT16 = 0
