IFPREVERB CLOSE -1
 IFITEM -1 OPEN
  ECHO PLAYER You replace the stones in their holding pouch, and cover all of the totem pictures.
  ECHO OTHERS %n replaces the stones in their holding pouch, and covers all of the totem pictures.
  SETITEMVAL -1 1 0
  SETITEMVAL -1 2 0
  SETITEMVAL -1 3 0
  SETITEMVAL -1 4 0
  SETITEMVAL -1 5 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT1 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT2 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT3 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT4 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT5 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT6 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT7 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT8 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT9 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT10 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT11 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT12 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT13 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT14 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT15 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT16 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT17 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT18 0
  EQUAL ITEMBIT19 0
 ENDIF
ENDIF


IFVERB RECALL -1
 IFVAR RAC = 2
  ECHO PLAYER You seem to recognize the ancestral Aelfen game of Kha'la'ra. 
  ECHO PLAYER The purpose of the game is to make all ten patterns with the bone pointers, by first pulling then turning them on alternating turns. 
  ECHO PLAYER Once a pattern is made, making it again before your opponent makes it allows you to place a scoring stone in your hollow.
  ECHO PLAYER The game officially ends when a player has uncovered all ten totems, and has more stones.
  ECHO PLAYER The two players must tap the box to join the game, or check their scores.
  ECHO PLAYER Closing the box will reset the game entirely.
  ECHO PLAYER Projecting your thoughts at it is customarily supposed to bring luck.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER It looks Aelfen.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PROJECT -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR FLAG4 = 1 
  IFVAR INTNUM57 > 0
   IFVAR INTNUM57 ! 9
    ECHO PLAYER You hold the pointers high, calling upon Snake, the luck totem!
    ECHO OTHERS %n holds the pointers high, calling out to Snake for luck!
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You hold the pointers high, calling upon your totem, Snake for his luck!
    ECHO OTHERS %n holds the pointers high, calling out in a hissing tongue!
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL The shadowy form of a serpent seems to entwine itself around the bone pointers!
   ENDIF
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You call upon the gods for luck!
   ECHO OTHERS %n calls upon the gods for luck!
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER It is bad form to disturb the flow of the game when you do not hold the pointers.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB KISS -1
 IFITEM -1 OPEN
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER You kiss the pointers in your hands for luck.
   ECHO OTHERS %n kisses the pointers in %h hands for luck.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You decide to wait until you hold the pointers to kiss them.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB RUB -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 OPEN
  ECHO PLAYER You rub the sides of the game box absentmindedly.
  ECHO OTHERS %n rubs the sides of the game box absentmindedly.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You painstakingly polish the fine wood of the box.
  ECHO OTHERS %n painstakingly polishes the fine wood of the box.
 ENDIF
ENDIF


IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
 IFITEM -1 OPEN
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR FLAG4 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER You focus all your mental energy on the throw.
   ECHO OTHERS %n furrows %h brow as %s prepares for the throw.
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER You watch the game intently.
   ECHO OTHERS %n watches the game intently.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  IFVAR RAC = 2
   CLEARVERB
   IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER As you lay hands upon it, you feel the box attuning to your spirit.
    ECHO OTHERS %n lays %h hands on the box, claiming it.
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 INTNUM3
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER As you lay hands upon it, you release the box from your possession.
    ECHO OTHERS %n lays %h hands on the box, releasing it.
    EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF


IFPREVERB GET -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 0
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! INTNUM3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The box seems to slide from your grasp.
   ECHO OTHERS %n tries to lift the box, but it slides from %h grasp.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB STEAL -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 0
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! INTNUM3
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The box seems to slide from your grasp.
   ECHO OTHERS %n tries to lift the box, but it slides from %h grasp.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

